WEBVTT

00:03.171 --> 00:05.573
Can you believe it's almost
Valentine's Day already?

00:05.606 --> 00:07.141
Remember
last Valentine's Day?

00:07.175 --> 00:10.378
We spent it getting
down and dirty
on the kitchen table.

00:10.411 --> 00:12.813
I can't wait to do that
with you again this year.

00:12.846 --> 00:16.184
Doing our taxes is the best way
to spend the holiday.

00:16.216 --> 00:17.718
Say "loophole."

00:17.751 --> 00:19.420
Loophole.

00:19.453 --> 00:20.988
[ Sighs ]

00:21.021 --> 00:24.858
Let's just make sure no stray
1099 forms were mailed late

00:24.892 --> 00:26.694
so we can get started.

00:27.895 --> 00:30.364
**

00:32.400 --> 00:34.335
What is it?

00:34.368 --> 00:37.338
Whatever it is,
it scares me.

00:37.371 --> 00:38.972
Go get the children.

00:41.575 --> 00:43.944
-- Captions by VITAC --

00:43.977 --> 00:45.113
* Fresh off the boat

00:45.146 --> 00:46.847
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

00:46.880 --> 00:49.117
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

00:49.150 --> 00:50.384
* Fresh off the boat

00:50.418 --> 00:52.720
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

00:52.753 --> 00:54.188
* But I know where I'm goin'

00:54.222 --> 00:57.024
* I'm fresh off the boat

00:57.057 --> 00:58.226
Bryson: So, let me
get this straight --

00:58.259 --> 01:01.562
you found this unwrapped,
uneaten pastrami sandwich

01:01.595 --> 01:02.696
in your mailbox?

01:02.730 --> 01:03.764
Yes.

01:03.797 --> 01:05.266
Just sitting there.

01:05.299 --> 01:06.600
What could this mean,
Officer Bryson?

01:06.634 --> 01:09.036
Is it a warning?
A threat?

01:09.069 --> 01:10.804
The flag was up.
They wanted us to find it.

01:10.838 --> 01:11.805
Who's "they"?

01:11.839 --> 01:14.142
We don't know!
That's your job!

01:14.175 --> 01:15.543
No one does their job.

01:15.576 --> 01:17.211
No one just does
a good job anymore.

01:17.245 --> 01:19.380
I just got a promotion,
actually.

01:19.413 --> 01:22.450
Anyway, mailbox sandwiches
really aren't a police matter.

01:22.483 --> 01:24.152
That's more of
a Neighborhood Watch thing.

01:24.185 --> 01:26.254
But our neighborhood
doesn't have one of those.

01:26.287 --> 01:28.289
That sounds interesting,
though.

01:28.322 --> 01:32.226
Watching your neighbors --
that's very Jessica.

01:32.260 --> 01:34.262
That's very Jessica.

01:34.295 --> 01:35.829
Thank you, Officer Bryson.

01:35.863 --> 01:38.199
Corporal Bryson.

01:39.700 --> 01:40.734
[ School bell rings ]

01:40.768 --> 01:42.436
**

01:42.470 --> 01:45.773
Okay, sirs, since I've become
a bit of a perv this year,

01:45.806 --> 01:47.741
I think it's only fitting
that I bring up

01:47.775 --> 01:49.610
this Friday's big dance
for discussion.

01:49.643 --> 01:50.644
Wait, what dance?

01:50.678 --> 01:52.480
Get your head
out of the clouds, Dave!

01:52.513 --> 01:53.581
I swear to God.

01:53.614 --> 01:55.082
The Valentine's Day dance.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.684
The Robin Scouts do it
as a fundraiser

01:56.717 --> 01:58.085
for all
the 8th- to 12th-graders

01:58.118 --> 01:59.753
in the East Orlando
school district.

01:59.787 --> 02:01.589
I hope the Robin Scouts
run a better dance

02:01.622 --> 02:03.424
than an organization.

02:03.457 --> 02:04.758
You guys are losers!

02:04.792 --> 02:07.595
No one likes you!
They like the cookies!

02:07.628 --> 02:09.597
You guys have
a flat management structure!

02:09.630 --> 02:11.632
How do you make decisions?!

02:11.665 --> 02:13.334
Walter: My sister Cordette
told me about it.

02:13.367 --> 02:15.769
Legend has it,
it's where everyone makes out.

02:15.803 --> 02:17.305
So you're saying
this is our best shot

02:17.338 --> 02:19.340
at getting our first kiss
before we start high school?

02:19.373 --> 02:20.774
Dave's awake, everyone.

02:20.808 --> 02:22.476
Everyone, Dave's awake.

02:22.510 --> 02:24.845
I remember my first kiss,
back in '93.

02:24.878 --> 02:26.680
'94?
It's hard to remember.

02:26.714 --> 02:28.716
I kissed lots of girls
back in D.C.

02:28.749 --> 02:30.117
I've never seen you
kiss Alison.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.653
Oh, yeah. She and I
haven't kissed yet.

02:32.686 --> 02:33.954
We're taking it slow,

02:33.987 --> 02:36.457
but I'm sure I'll lay a few
on her at the dance.

02:36.490 --> 02:39.460
The only light is a disco ball
and one floor lamp.

02:39.493 --> 02:41.962
There are dark,
unsupervised slut pockets

02:41.995 --> 02:44.164
all over
that Jewish Community Center.

02:44.198 --> 02:47.735
**

02:47.768 --> 02:49.503
Peter and I just wanted
to thank everyone

02:49.537 --> 02:51.472
for the generous
welcome-to-the-neighborhood

02:51.505 --> 02:54.408
lawn frog decoration
you gave us.

02:54.442 --> 02:56.344
Frogs are
my favorite animals --

02:56.377 --> 02:59.713
after giraffes and elephants
and monkeys.

02:59.747 --> 03:03.050
Humans are low on the list.

03:03.083 --> 03:04.885
Okay, thank you, Peter.

03:04.918 --> 03:06.854
We'll...put that
in the notes.

03:06.887 --> 03:07.988
And it's our pleasure, Ann.

03:08.021 --> 03:09.323
Sorry it took so long
to get to you,

03:09.357 --> 03:11.692
but not everyone pitched in
their share on time.

03:11.725 --> 03:13.193
Thankfully,
Evan stepped up

03:13.227 --> 03:15.396
and covered
our straggler's last $12.

03:16.464 --> 03:19.267
Let me guess --
you sti don't have it.

03:19.300 --> 03:20.601
I forgot -- again.

03:20.634 --> 03:23.337
I'm sorry, Evan.
Next time, I promise.

03:23.371 --> 03:25.273
Mommy brain.
[ Groans ]

03:25.306 --> 03:26.440
[ Exhales slowly ]

03:26.474 --> 03:28.376
Okay, well,
if that's everything, then...

03:28.409 --> 03:31.245
Actually, I have a serious issue
I would like to discuss.

03:32.480 --> 03:33.947
Our home was attacked.

03:33.981 --> 03:35.249
[ People gasp ]

03:35.283 --> 03:36.950
Yes. That's right.

03:36.984 --> 03:39.687
My husband and I went
to check the mail,

03:39.720 --> 03:42.189
and we found...

03:42.222 --> 03:45.192
[ Voice breaking ]
a pastrami sandwich
just sitting in our mailbox.

03:45.225 --> 03:47.194
It was freaky.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.229
That is why I propose

03:49.263 --> 03:51.532
that we start
a Neighborhood Watch.

03:51.565 --> 03:53.967
I know some of you may think
I'm overreacting,

03:54.001 --> 03:55.469
like the police did,
but I --

03:55.503 --> 03:57.137
Like hell we do.

03:57.170 --> 03:58.972
I don't want a sandwich
in my mailbox.

03:59.006 --> 03:59.907
Who does?

03:59.940 --> 04:01.775
Really?

04:01.809 --> 04:04.612
Oh, this is amazing.
I have so many great ideas.

04:04.645 --> 04:05.979
Fantastic.

04:06.013 --> 04:08.416
We'll put it on the agenda
for next week's HOA meeting.

04:08.449 --> 04:09.417
Thank you, Jessica.

04:09.450 --> 04:13.887
**

04:13.921 --> 04:15.222
"Mommy brain"?

04:15.255 --> 04:16.790
I guess having a kid
gives you permission

04:16.824 --> 04:18.257
to disrespect people.

04:18.291 --> 04:19.892
Evan, when you...
Lend someone money,

04:19.927 --> 04:22.463
you have to be okay
with never getting it back.

04:22.496 --> 04:24.798
I know, I know.

04:24.832 --> 04:27.067
Louis, hey, come look
at the great ideas I have

04:27.100 --> 04:28.268
for the Neighborhood Watch.

04:28.302 --> 04:30.237
Wow. Are those
security cameras?
Yes.

04:30.270 --> 04:33.841
I'm also proposing
a volunteer nightly patrol shift

04:33.874 --> 04:37.578
and an anonymous tip line
that will ring directly to me.

04:37.611 --> 04:38.746
"J. Huang.

04:38.779 --> 04:40.013
A bandit?

04:40.047 --> 04:41.749
Use the Tasers
I distributed.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.584
Zap him in the area."

04:43.617 --> 04:44.452
Hmm.

04:54.962 --> 04:57.631
Grandma, you should really
keep your money in the bank.

04:57.665 --> 04:58.999
It's not safe
in the house.

05:01.469 --> 05:03.203
Oh, Grandma.

05:03.236 --> 05:05.138
Dear, sweet Grandma.

05:05.172 --> 05:08.275
You have no idea
what hell you hath unlocked.

05:08.308 --> 05:10.611
I even came up with
a very clever name for it --

05:10.644 --> 05:13.481
"Neighborhood Watch
Association" -- N.W.A.

05:13.514 --> 05:15.716
How's that, now?
Y'all talking Dre?

05:15.749 --> 05:16.950
Neighborhood Watch.

05:16.984 --> 05:18.285
Oh.

05:18.318 --> 05:21.321
I'd pick a new name, Mom.
N.W.A. is already a thing.

05:21.355 --> 05:22.556
What's it stand for?

05:25.493 --> 05:27.227
I can't say.

05:27.260 --> 05:29.329
**

05:31.432 --> 05:32.500
Trent!

05:34.101 --> 05:35.869
Eddie.
It's not a good time.

05:35.903 --> 05:38.539
Your mom's not a good time.
Let me in.

05:40.608 --> 05:42.175
I need to borrow
the group bottle of Polo cologne

05:42.209 --> 05:43.310
for the dance.

05:43.343 --> 05:46.146
I'm gonna
pre-spray my clothes, so --

05:46.179 --> 05:47.915
Spa day --
that's what's good.

05:47.948 --> 05:49.650
I'm really busy right now,
Eddie.

05:49.683 --> 05:50.518
What's that?

05:50.551 --> 05:51.885
Nothing!
No, don't --

05:52.853 --> 05:54.488
"Sparrow Scout Handbook"?

05:54.522 --> 05:58.392
**

05:58.426 --> 05:59.259
No --

06:00.728 --> 06:01.895
What the hell, Trent?!

06:01.929 --> 06:03.731
I thought you said
you hated the Scouts.

06:03.764 --> 06:05.265
I only said that
so no one would suspect

06:05.298 --> 06:07.435
that I myself am a Scout.

06:07.468 --> 06:09.503
Everybody makes fun
of Sparrow Scouts,

06:09.537 --> 06:11.338
and I've built a reputation
as a cool person.

06:11.371 --> 06:13.006
Why do you need the cologne,
anyways?

06:13.040 --> 06:15.709
I thought you weren't nervous
about the dance.

06:15.743 --> 06:16.844
[ Sighs ]

06:16.877 --> 06:18.712
Since you're coming clean
with secrets

06:18.746 --> 06:22.215
and you're a Sparrow Scout,
I can obviously trust you.

06:22.249 --> 06:24.184
I lied about kissing girls
in D.C.

06:24.217 --> 06:25.453
I've never kissed a girl.

06:25.486 --> 06:26.787
[ Gasps ]

06:26.820 --> 06:28.221
[ Car door closes ]

06:31.759 --> 06:38.766
**

06:39.066 --> 06:41.234
Hey, great!
They did your idea!

06:41.268 --> 06:43.904
Yes -- my idea.

06:43.937 --> 06:45.238
I was gonna head it up.

06:45.272 --> 06:47.040
And they said
that we would discuss it

06:47.074 --> 06:48.909
at the next HOA meeting.

06:48.942 --> 06:51.044
I'm sure this is all
just a misunderstanding.

06:51.078 --> 06:53.213
No way. I know
exactly what's going on here.

06:53.246 --> 06:55.783
Those HOA ladies
don't think

06:55.816 --> 06:59.386
I would be good
at leading a Neighborhood Watch.

06:59.419 --> 07:00.921
But I see everything.

07:00.954 --> 07:04.592
I'll show them I am amazing
at finding things.

07:06.093 --> 07:07.227
Jessica: There he is.

07:07.260 --> 07:08.462
[ Click ]

07:08.496 --> 07:09.597
There he is.

07:09.630 --> 07:11.431
[ Click ]

07:11.465 --> 07:12.432
There he is.

07:12.466 --> 07:13.634
[ Click ]

07:13.667 --> 07:15.002
Candy cane, candy cane,
candy cane...

07:15.035 --> 07:16.069
There he is!

07:16.103 --> 07:19.439
Hey, Jessica?
Can I have a word?

07:19.473 --> 07:20.608
[ Projector stops ]

07:20.641 --> 07:22.142
I think
you're missing the point.

07:22.175 --> 07:24.144
Nobody doubts your ability
to find Waldo.

07:24.177 --> 07:25.479
Thank you.

07:25.513 --> 07:26.980
We don't want you involved
in the Neighborhood Watch

07:27.014 --> 07:28.348
because you're not
a team player.

07:28.381 --> 07:29.817
**

07:35.222 --> 07:36.323
[ Sighs ]
I can't believe that's why

07:36.356 --> 07:38.425
they excluded me
from the Neighborhood Watch.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.961
Who cares
if I'm not a team player?

07:40.994 --> 07:42.863
That cantaloupe
is supposed to last all week.

07:42.896 --> 07:45.533
What's wrong
with being a team leader?

07:45.566 --> 07:48.135
Some people row,
some people coxswain.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.171
I just rented
"Oxford Blues."

07:51.204 --> 07:54.441
Best rowing movie
I've seen in a while.

07:54.474 --> 07:58.045
Okay, I found
a Monopoly hat piece,

07:58.078 --> 07:59.312
Evan's diary,

07:59.346 --> 08:01.515
and an R-rated pen
in Dad's closet.

08:05.553 --> 08:07.220
It's in
Mom and Dad's room!

08:07.254 --> 08:08.321
I knew it!

08:14.061 --> 08:15.462
[ Sighs ]

08:15.495 --> 08:17.798
Jessica, if you want to be a
part of the Neighborhood Watch,

08:17.831 --> 08:21.134
you're going to have to learn
to be a team player.

08:21.168 --> 08:22.570
Don't worry.
I'll help you.

08:22.603 --> 08:24.004
[ Sighs ]

08:25.038 --> 08:26.907
All right,
talk to me, Eddie.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.576
Why haven't you
kissed a girl yet?

08:28.609 --> 08:31.078
Well, the truth is --

08:31.111 --> 08:32.813
Ugh! What is this?!

08:32.846 --> 08:35.148
It's parve.
My mom keeps kosher.

08:35.182 --> 08:36.583
I thought you knew that.

08:37.551 --> 08:39.019
Well, the truth is,

08:39.052 --> 08:41.154
I've had this perfect image
in my head about my first kiss

08:41.188 --> 08:42.890
ever since I saw
"Poetic Justice,"

08:42.923 --> 08:44.157
starring Tupac as Lucky
and...

08:44.191 --> 08:45.759
Janet Jackson as Justice.

08:45.793 --> 08:47.227
Yes, I know it well.

08:47.260 --> 08:49.229
Tupac and Janet share
a tender kiss on the beach.

08:49.262 --> 08:51.331
Right?
It was bomb.

08:51.364 --> 08:52.866
[ Sighs ]
I know it's kind of dumb

08:52.900 --> 08:55.335
and it's not gonna be
 exactly like that,

08:55.368 --> 08:58.005
but I'm waiting
for the right moment.

08:58.038 --> 08:59.072
I love that.

08:59.106 --> 09:01.274
And the right moment
is Valentine's Day.

09:01.308 --> 09:03.677
You heard the guys --
This is my best shot

09:03.711 --> 09:05.746
to get my first kiss
before 9th grade.

09:05.779 --> 09:07.781
I can't go into high school
a kissing virgin!

09:07.815 --> 09:09.016
Eddie, relax.

09:09.049 --> 09:11.351
Above all, Sparrow Scouts
are loyal friends.

09:11.384 --> 09:12.519
I'm gonna be
your wingman.

09:12.552 --> 09:14.387
I know you and Alison
as a couple.

09:14.421 --> 09:16.590
I guess you did spend
last Valentine's Day with us.

09:16.624 --> 09:18.291
At the Janet Jackson
concert.

09:18.325 --> 09:20.460
Full conversational circle.

09:20.493 --> 09:22.562
Don't worry.
We're gonna get you kissed.

09:24.397 --> 09:26.800
Now, we're both gonna
cut our hands and join our blood

09:26.834 --> 09:28.435
so we never forget
this bond of shared secrets.

09:28.468 --> 09:29.937
I'm not doing that.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.706
Okay, if you're going to be
a team player,

09:32.740 --> 09:35.075
you have to learn how to deal
with challenging teammates.

09:35.108 --> 09:37.978
So what do you do if someone
disagrees with your idea?

09:38.011 --> 09:39.312
Well,
why would they do that?

09:39.346 --> 09:42.082
[ Sighs ] Okay.
Just pretend I'm the HOA.

09:42.115 --> 09:44.217
Tell me an idea you have
for the Neighborhood Watch.

09:44.251 --> 09:46.386
I think we should
put up security cameras

09:46.419 --> 09:47.487
in the cul-de-sac.

09:47.520 --> 09:48.822
No, that's too expensive.

09:48.856 --> 09:52.092
We buy them wholesale using
funds from the October car wash!

09:52.125 --> 09:54.928
Would I have suggested it if
I hadn't already done the math?

09:55.929 --> 09:57.564
We have work to do.

09:57.597 --> 09:59.599
What do you do
if someone suggests an idea

09:59.633 --> 10:01.501
that's worse than yours?

10:01.534 --> 10:04.171
I think we should start
a volunteer nightly patrol.

10:07.841 --> 10:09.609
Uh-huh. And who will tend
to the children

10:09.643 --> 10:12.112
that get maimed
in the streets, Jenny?

10:13.313 --> 10:15.348
What do you do
if you suggest an idea,

10:15.382 --> 10:17.250
then someone else suggests
the same idea

10:17.284 --> 10:19.019
and they get credit
for it?

10:19.052 --> 10:22.089
I also think we should set up
an anonymous tip line.

10:22.122 --> 10:24.124
I had an idea
for your Neighborhood Watch.

10:24.157 --> 10:26.259
What if you set up
a phone number people can call

10:26.293 --> 10:28.428
to report suspicious activity
in the neighborhood?

10:28.461 --> 10:29.730
That's my idea!

10:30.998 --> 10:36.169
I mean, uh, maybe you can have
the same idea as me --

10:36.203 --> 10:37.604
after me --

10:37.637 --> 10:39.707
because you're slower...

10:39.740 --> 10:40.808
mentally.

10:41.909 --> 10:44.111
And that is why
surveillance cameras,

10:44.144 --> 10:47.147
nightly patrol shifts,
and an anonymous tip line

10:47.180 --> 10:49.016
would increase security

10:49.049 --> 10:51.852
and decrease mailbox sandwiches
in our neighborhood.

10:51.885 --> 10:53.954
[ High-pitched ] We could also
publish a newsletter

10:53.987 --> 10:56.123
to update everyone
on our progress.

10:56.156 --> 10:57.858
My hair is red.

10:57.891 --> 10:59.359
Great idea, Lisa.

10:59.392 --> 11:00.894
Let's definitely do that.

11:00.928 --> 11:02.162
[ Normal voice ]
You're ready.

11:02.195 --> 11:03.864
[ Sighs ]

11:05.265 --> 11:07.134
It was really tough.

11:07.167 --> 11:10.137
We both said some things
we didn't mean, and some we did.

11:10.170 --> 11:12.806
But I refuse to call my divorce
a failed marriage.

11:12.840 --> 11:15.142
[ Voice breaking ] We made
a beautiful child together,

11:15.175 --> 11:17.945
and if that's not a success,
I don't know what is.

11:19.079 --> 11:21.081
So, I'm wondering
if there's any childcare

11:21.114 --> 11:22.349
available
in the neighborhood.

11:22.382 --> 11:24.151
I work two jobs,
and I can't always be there

11:24.184 --> 11:26.553
when Peter gets home
from school.

11:26.586 --> 11:28.421
I don't prefer
to be touched.

11:29.857 --> 11:31.324
You know,
I've thought about it,

11:31.358 --> 11:33.927
and it's okay if you don't
pay me back the $12.

11:33.961 --> 11:35.695
What's important
is that Ann and Peter

11:35.729 --> 11:37.931
feel welcome
in the neighborhood.

11:37.965 --> 11:39.599
Mm-hmm.

11:39.632 --> 11:43.036
Carol-Joan,
are those new sandals?

11:43.070 --> 11:46.406
Did you buy new sandals
when you know you owe me $12?

11:46.439 --> 11:50.343
I had your money,
but I-I had to tip my colorist.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.245
So, that's it
for the HOA.

11:52.279 --> 11:54.047
The Neighborhood Watch committee
will be staying after

11:54.081 --> 11:56.316
to discuss the success
of the signs we put up.

12:00.954 --> 12:03.190
So, Jessica,
whenever you're ready

12:03.223 --> 12:04.858
to [clicks tongue] leave...
[ Chuckles ]

12:04.892 --> 12:06.960
Actually,
I would like to stay.

12:06.994 --> 12:09.029
I have a couple of ideas

12:09.062 --> 12:11.264
I would like
to constructively add

12:11.298 --> 12:14.802
to all of
your already-great ideas.

12:14.835 --> 12:16.669
Um...okay.

12:19.840 --> 12:22.542
So, I've done
some research,

12:22.575 --> 12:23.777
and I think
the Neighborhood Watch

12:23.811 --> 12:26.579
could be even better
if we add security cameras,

12:26.613 --> 12:27.881
a nightly patrol --

12:27.915 --> 12:30.217
Mm, yeah,
we're not doing any of that.

12:30.250 --> 12:31.718
Oh, well,
just hear me out.

12:31.751 --> 12:35.288
It's just that there have been
no new sandwiches in mailboxes,

12:35.322 --> 12:38.058
so the signs
seem to be working.

12:38.091 --> 12:40.060
She worked really hard
on these ideas.

12:40.093 --> 12:41.895
If you'll just listen --
You know what?
Never mind.

12:41.929 --> 12:43.230
Meeting is adjourned.

12:43.263 --> 12:45.732
And to the saboteur
who brought the cheesecake bars,

12:45.765 --> 12:46.900
you can take them with you.

12:46.934 --> 12:48.068
They'll be by the door.

12:48.101 --> 12:50.203
You know I'm getting ready
for bikini season.

12:52.172 --> 12:53.506
Forget it, Louis.

12:53.540 --> 12:57.310
They're never gonna let me be
part of the Neighborhood Watch.

12:57.344 --> 12:59.913
I'm gonna stop at 7-Eleven
for a Chipwich.

12:59.947 --> 13:01.081
I'll see you at home.

13:01.114 --> 13:04.417
**

13:04.451 --> 13:06.453
I feel so bad
for your mom.

13:06.486 --> 13:08.755
She did such a good job
learning to be a team player,

13:08.788 --> 13:10.423
but she wasn't rewarded
for it.

13:10.457 --> 13:12.926
The set of eggs
Carol-Joan has on her,

13:12.960 --> 13:15.162
to wear her brand-new sandals
in front of me.

13:15.195 --> 13:16.596
They kept saying
"The signs are enough.

13:16.629 --> 13:17.931
The signs are enough."

13:17.965 --> 13:19.166
Go to an ATM!

13:19.199 --> 13:22.669
Put on your new sandals
and walk to an ATM!

13:22.702 --> 13:26.139
**

13:26.173 --> 13:27.707
Maybe they'd hear Jessica out

13:27.740 --> 13:29.776
if they thought
the signs weren't enough.

13:29.809 --> 13:33.580
I don't understand women
with unpainted toenails.

13:39.987 --> 13:41.321
Here you go.

13:41.354 --> 13:42.355
I'm bugging out.

13:42.389 --> 13:43.523
Don't bug out.

13:43.556 --> 13:45.292
You'll take Alison
to the roof of the building

13:45.325 --> 13:46.559
and use this telescope
to show her

13:46.593 --> 13:48.028
the star that you paid
to name after her.

13:48.061 --> 13:49.963
And then I'm gonna pop
a "kiss me" Sweetheart

13:49.997 --> 13:51.798
and I'm gonna kiss her.

13:51.831 --> 13:52.699
Hey, Eddie.

13:52.732 --> 13:53.700
Hey, Trent.

13:53.733 --> 13:55.235
You guys ready
to go inside?

13:55.268 --> 13:56.536
We're ready.

14:00.373 --> 14:01.975
Well, well, well.

14:02.009 --> 14:04.511
Look who wants
to come into our house.

14:04.544 --> 14:06.046
Walk away, Scout hater.

14:06.079 --> 14:08.848
No way any of you
are coming into our dance.

14:10.717 --> 14:13.486
And here's the thing about
flat management structure --

14:13.520 --> 14:16.689
if you come after one of us,
you get all of us.

14:16.723 --> 14:17.757
Mm-hmm.

14:19.692 --> 14:21.661
[ Siren wails ]

14:21.694 --> 14:23.363
[ Police radio chatter ]

14:23.396 --> 14:24.864
Oh, my God.

14:26.266 --> 14:28.235
Corporal Bryson,
what happened?

14:28.268 --> 14:29.502
Sad day, Louis.

14:29.536 --> 14:33.506
It appears someone stole
Ann's ceramic lawn frog.

14:33.540 --> 14:37.277
This seems a little excessive
for a stolen yard decoration.

14:37.310 --> 14:40.747
It was also a hide-a-key
for her latchkey son, Peter.

14:40.780 --> 14:41.781
He's missing.

14:47.220 --> 14:48.188
Something horrible happened.

14:48.221 --> 14:49.689
Ann's son, Peter,
is missing.

14:49.722 --> 14:50.958
What?!

14:50.991 --> 14:53.626
Why can't these white people
keep track of their kids?

14:53.660 --> 14:55.095
Every time we look
at a milk carton,

14:55.128 --> 14:57.597
we have to see
their failures.

14:57.630 --> 14:59.899
Okay.
Let's go to the tapes.

14:59.933 --> 15:03.203
**

15:03.236 --> 15:06.139
You put up an unsanctioned
security camera?
Mm.

15:06.173 --> 15:07.975
I thought you learned
how to be a team player.

15:08.008 --> 15:09.242
I did.

15:09.276 --> 15:10.978
But if the team doesn't
go along with what you want,

15:11.011 --> 15:12.579
you got to do
your own thing.

15:12.612 --> 15:15.548
**

15:15.582 --> 15:18.051
Okay, so, the Robin Scouts
won't let us in the dance.

15:18.085 --> 15:19.786
Feels dramatic, but sure.

15:19.819 --> 15:20.954
Here's the new plan --

15:20.988 --> 15:22.289
I know a burger place
down the street

15:22.322 --> 15:24.291
that lets you dictate
the number of straws you get.

15:24.324 --> 15:26.126
We go there,
you and Alison get two straws,

15:26.159 --> 15:27.727
and you share
a romantic milkshake.

15:27.760 --> 15:29.062
Yeah, yeah, that's good!

15:29.096 --> 15:30.663
And I still have
the Sweethearts.

15:30.697 --> 15:32.899
This night
can still be perfect.

15:32.932 --> 15:35.135
Now, we're both gonna cut
our hands and join our blood --

15:35.168 --> 15:36.669
Dude, stop.

15:39.039 --> 15:41.408
I found it.
I found your money.

15:41.441 --> 15:42.942
It was in
Evan's underwear drawer.

15:50.984 --> 15:52.685
The camera was recording
the whole day

15:52.719 --> 15:54.121
that Peter went missing.

16:01.628 --> 16:02.962
I stole the lawn frog.

16:02.996 --> 16:04.097
What?

16:04.131 --> 16:05.598
I thought that
if something went missing,

16:05.632 --> 16:07.600
the Neighborhood Watch would see
their signs weren't enough

16:07.634 --> 16:09.669
and listen
to your great ideas.

16:09.702 --> 16:11.338
But I didn't mean
for the thing that went missing

16:11.371 --> 16:12.639
to be a child.

16:12.672 --> 16:15.042
You got a child kidnapped?

16:16.376 --> 16:19.612
That is the sweetest thing
you've ever done for me.

16:19.646 --> 16:20.613
[ Gasps ]

16:20.647 --> 16:22.515
You're not mad?
No.

16:22.549 --> 16:25.985
You really want me to have
the things I want in life.

16:26.019 --> 16:29.022
And you'll do whatever
you have to to help me get them.

16:29.056 --> 16:31.358
I'm never gonna be mad at you
for that.

16:33.360 --> 16:35.862
Now let's see what happened
to that little snowball.

16:38.165 --> 16:39.666
Marvin?

16:43.203 --> 16:44.704
[ Gasps ] Look.

16:48.241 --> 16:49.809
Hey, sweetie!

16:49.842 --> 16:51.911
Mwah! Mwah!

16:51.944 --> 16:53.313
I did it.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.415
I put the sandwich
in your mailbox.

16:55.448 --> 16:56.916
Why would you do that?

16:56.949 --> 16:58.351
Well, I went to the doctor
last week,

16:58.385 --> 17:01.721
and she told me
that I had high blood pressure.

17:01.754 --> 17:03.490
Now I have to sneak
my sandwiches

17:03.523 --> 17:06.326
'cause Honey won't let me
eat cured meats anymore.

17:06.358 --> 17:07.926
But she keeps popping up
out of nowhere,

17:07.960 --> 17:09.662
like a sexy
jack-in-the-box.

17:09.695 --> 17:10.663
I can't believe this.

17:10.696 --> 17:11.698
I know --

17:11.731 --> 17:13.266
a lady doctor.

17:13.300 --> 17:14.501
[ Chuckles ]

17:14.534 --> 17:17.002
Oh, she's good, though.
She's not half bad.

17:17.036 --> 17:19.172
I'm sorry -- Why are we solving
the sandwich case

17:19.205 --> 17:20.406
when there's
a child missing?

17:20.440 --> 17:22.742
Marvin, did you see Peter
when you were outside

17:22.775 --> 17:24.010
eating your sneaky sandwich?

17:24.042 --> 17:25.178
I did.

17:25.212 --> 17:27.012
He asked me where he could get
a new house key,

17:27.046 --> 17:28.581
and I told him there was
a locksmith at the mall.

17:28.615 --> 17:30.049
So he couldn't
find his key

17:30.083 --> 17:32.452
and thought he could go
to the mall and get one made?

17:32.485 --> 17:34.254
And you just let him go
by himself?

17:34.287 --> 17:37.257
Well, the boy's 17 years old.
He can go where he pleases.

17:37.290 --> 17:39.025
He's 10.

17:39.058 --> 17:40.460
Oh.

17:40.493 --> 17:44.631
**

17:44.664 --> 17:45.798
[ Sighs ]

17:47.300 --> 17:48.801
We'll never
find Peter here.

17:48.835 --> 17:50.303
Jessica,
there's no way --
There he is!

17:54.174 --> 17:54.974
Huh.

17:55.007 --> 17:57.777
**

18:02.849 --> 18:05.552
You look really pretty, Alison.
I like your hair like that.

18:05.585 --> 18:07.687
Thanks. It's the same way
I always wear it.

18:09.122 --> 18:11.424
Even though we didn't
get to go to the dance,

18:11.458 --> 18:14.427
this has been a really great
Valentine's Day, Eddie.

18:14.461 --> 18:15.762
I'm glad you said that.

18:18.298 --> 18:21.334
[ Janet Jackson's "Again"
plays ]

18:24.271 --> 18:26.473
[ Chokes ]

18:26.506 --> 18:27.840
Eddie? Are you okay?

18:27.874 --> 18:29.476
[ Gasps ] Oh, no.

18:29.509 --> 18:31.311
Time to make
the Boys In Beige proud!

18:33.946 --> 18:35.582
What are you doing,
Trent?!

18:35.615 --> 18:37.016
It's okay!
I earned a badge for this!

18:37.049 --> 18:38.518
Now get back, Olsen!

18:38.551 --> 18:39.586
I got you, buddy.

18:39.619 --> 18:40.587
[ Inhales ]

18:40.620 --> 18:42.789
[ Weakly ]
Unh-unh.

18:49.862 --> 18:50.997
[ Gasps ]

18:52.031 --> 18:53.266
[ Sighs ]

18:53.300 --> 18:56.236
It's always just the three of us
on Valentine's Day, huh?

18:59.506 --> 19:01.208
I can't thank you enough.

19:01.241 --> 19:02.809
Of course.
We're happy to help.

19:02.842 --> 19:04.143
I just hope
they find that monster

19:04.177 --> 19:05.612
who stole
our hide-a-key frog.

19:05.645 --> 19:07.447
Yep, no problem. Good thing
you have a Neighborhood Watch.

19:07.480 --> 19:09.115
Bye.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

19:09.148 --> 19:11.951
Let's not tell Daddy about this,
okay, sweetums?

19:11.984 --> 19:14.487
Okay. I won't tell Tanya,
either.

19:14.521 --> 19:15.488
Tanya?

19:15.522 --> 19:17.156
Who the hell's Tanya?

19:17.190 --> 19:19.726
You were really amazing
today.

19:19.759 --> 19:22.795
We never would've found Peter
without you.

19:22.829 --> 19:26.065
Those neighborhood ladies may
not think you're a team player,

19:26.098 --> 19:28.535
but I'd pick you for my team
every time.

19:32.405 --> 19:34.807
It's nice being on a team
with you, too.

19:34.841 --> 19:36.843
If you didn't
screw things up so bad,

19:36.876 --> 19:38.811
I wouldn't look so good
fixing them.

19:38.845 --> 19:40.547
Hey, this wasn't
all my fault.

19:40.580 --> 19:42.982
Peter thinks he can buy
a key to his house at the mall.

19:43.015 --> 19:44.150
[ Both laugh ]

19:44.183 --> 19:45.418
And how about Marvin?

19:45.452 --> 19:47.320
Why doesn't he eat
all the sandwiches he wants

19:47.354 --> 19:48.555
when he's at work?

19:48.588 --> 19:49.722
[ Both laugh ]

19:49.756 --> 19:52.492
We are the only smart people
in this neighborhood.

19:52.525 --> 19:54.294
Mm.

19:55.528 --> 19:57.163
I'm sorry about tonight.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.065
I really wanted it
to be special.

19:59.098 --> 20:01.100
Well,
the night's not over.

20:01.133 --> 20:02.569
[ "Again" plays ]

20:02.602 --> 20:05.037
* I heard from a friend today

20:05.071 --> 20:08.341
* And she said
you were in town *

20:08.375 --> 20:10.743
* Suddenly, the memories --

20:10.777 --> 20:12.178
Hey, Alison!

20:12.211 --> 20:13.880
How are my sloppy seconds?

20:13.913 --> 20:15.815
[ Laughs ]

20:21.454 --> 20:22.555
[ Doorbell rings ]

20:24.324 --> 20:26.293
Well, hey, there,
big door answerer.

20:26.326 --> 20:27.394
We're here
to see your mom.

20:27.427 --> 20:29.362
Sure --
if you pay the toll.

20:29.396 --> 20:30.863
It's $12.

20:30.897 --> 20:37.704
**

20:37.737 --> 20:39.205
I'll get your change --

20:39.238 --> 20:40.206
eventually.

20:40.239 --> 20:41.207
[ Huffs ]

20:41.240 --> 20:43.376
Deidre. CJ.

20:43.410 --> 20:44.577
Hey, Jessica.

20:44.611 --> 20:46.446
So, we heard about
how you found Peter.

20:46.479 --> 20:48.481
We just want to say
we are so sorry

20:48.515 --> 20:51.117
that we did not listen
to all your great ideas.

20:51.150 --> 20:52.919
You obviously know
what you're doing.

20:52.952 --> 20:54.321
So we wanted
to invite you

20:54.354 --> 20:56.289
to head up
the Neighborhood Watch.

20:56.323 --> 20:58.124
Your committee,
your rules.

20:58.157 --> 20:59.125
Really?

21:01.127 --> 21:02.895
Wow. I would love that.

21:02.929 --> 21:03.996
Thank you.

21:04.030 --> 21:05.164
You're both fired.

21:05.197 --> 21:06.232
What?

21:06.265 --> 21:07.667
A kid went missing
on your watch.

21:07.700 --> 21:10.102
Clearly, I am the only person
I can count on around here.

21:10.136 --> 21:11.738
Security will escort you out.

21:11.771 --> 21:13.940
[ Both sputter angrily ]

21:13.973 --> 21:16.075
Has anyone seen
my HOA money box?

21:16.108 --> 21:18.244
It's not in my underwear drawer,
where I left it.

21:18.277 --> 21:20.046
Evan!

21:27.286 --> 21:28.455
You.

21:28.488 --> 21:30.490
[ Chuckles ]
